OL,3,CHow Andy Burnham's first day as Prime
OL,4,CMinister unfolded
OL,6,FIn his first speech outside Downing
OL,7,FStreet, Mr Burnham promised to provide
OL,8,Fearly "breathing space" for households
OL,9,Fstruggling with the cost of living,
OL,10,Fvowed to end rough sleeping and set
OL,11,Fout his ambition to "reindustrialise
OL,12,FBritain".
OL,14,FThe new PM said he would deliver "a
OL,15,Fnew political model and a new economic
OL,16,Fmodel" for Britain.
OL,26,@pD@GOUpD@WO]sD@UOUtD@HO]vD@bOUxD@FO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784605665
OL,3,CHow Andy Burnham's first day as Prime
OL,4,CMinister unfolded
OL,6,FIt was, he said, a time for
OL,7,F"reflection and new resolution",
OL,8,Fadding that: "Britain needs to show
OL,9,Fthe world that we can regain our
OL,10,Fstability once again".
OL,12,FHe continued: "I know people at home
OL,13,Fare fed up with politics. I hear you
OL,14,Fand I want to be honest with you ` we
OL,15,Fhave not been good enough, and we need
OL,16,Fto be better. We will be.
OL,26,@oD@AOUoD@_O]pD@NOUrD@UO]tD@OOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784605665
OL,3,CHow Andy Burnham's first day as Prime
OL,4,CMinister unfolded
OL,6,F"We will make this moment a circuit
OL,7,Fbreaker for Britain, bringing forward
OL,8,Fthe biggest changes in the last 40
OL,9,Fyears ` a new political model and a
OL,10,Fnew economic model."
OL,12,FSir John Healey became Mr Burnham's
OL,13,Fmajor appointment, taking over as
OL,14,FChancellor of the Exchequer.
OL,16,FIn a statement posted on X, he said:
OL,17,F"It is the greatest privilege to be
OL,18,Fappointed Chancellor of the Exchequer
OL,19,Fby the Prime Minister.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@TO]yD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1784605665
OL,3,CHow Andy Burnham's first day as Prime
OL,4,CMinister unfolded
OL,6,F"Together, we will build a new
OL,7,Feconomy, build new hope and advance
OL,8,Fthe working people of this country.
OL,10,F"Time to get on with the job."
OL,12,FThe reshaped Cabinet saw former Labour
OL,13,Fleader Ed Miliband appointed Foreign
OL,14,FSecretary, while Yvette Cooper moved
OL,15,Fto the health brief.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUrD@^O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
